Time-series forecasting (TSF) finds broad applications in real-world scenarios. Due to the dynamic nature of
time-series data, it is crucial for TSF models to preserve out-of-distribution (OOD) generalization abilities, as
training and test sets represent historical and future data respectively. In this paper, we aim to alleviate the
inherent OOD problem in TSF via invariant learning. We identify fundamental challenges of invariant learning for
